&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for a Band 5 Nurse to join our T9 South ward Team. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;T9 South is a 32 bedded male and female ward within the GI Division looking after surgical/medical patients in the following specialities:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;- Upper GI surgery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;- Vascular surgery &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;- Hepatobiliary pancreatic Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;- Bariatric &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;- GI medicine&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Whilst working on T9 South you will benefit from a comprehensive induction programme, GI Ward education days and other study days to enhance your clinical skills and knowledge. A dedicated Clinical Practice Facilitator who will help oversee your skills and professional development. On top of this, we may be able to offer a rotation to our 2 other GI wards specialising in colorectal surgery and Intestinal Failure/GI Medicine. We have an excellent track record of promoting our band 5s to band 6 and associate CNS roles. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is an acute ward but with rewarding benefits and outstanding teamwork.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please make sure you are available on the following assessment day:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assessment date: TBC&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you feel this is something you will be interested in then please contact the ward sister – Betty Diangkinay betty.diangkinay@nhs.net. Informal visits are encouraged for short-listed candidates.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
